  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/sa/hemolysis-sensitivity-vad",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Sobol sensitivity analysis — hemolysis NIH drivers",
    "description": "First- and total-order Sobol indices computed across the Monte Carlo ensemble (n=2000) for five uncertain inputs: inlet velocity profile shape, blood viscosity, hemolysis model power-law exponent, hemolysis model coefficient, and turbulence model constant C_mu. The hemolysis model coefficient dominates (S1=0.61, ST=0.67); turbulence model constant contributes ST=0.18 at the 3.0 L/min set-point where shear stress gradients are steepest. Inlet velocity profile and viscosity each contribute ST < 0.08, confirming that targeted experimental characterisation of the hemolysis model constants would most efficiently reduce prediction uncertainty."
  },
